Feb 17 2004	Excellent Value/A Real Find	Our family booked 2 rooms at the Rushmore for 10 days over Christmas 2003. I used trip advisor to make my decision to rent. It was truly an excellent find for London lodging. Our rooms were spacious with roomy bathrooms (great water pressure and temperature) and coffee/tea in room. Mind you, this is not a fancy boutique hotel but it offers so many advantages I think you will be hard pressed to find better London accomodation for anywhere near the money. The staircase is narrow and there are no elevators. However we had one attic room (4th floor) and it was definitely worth the climb. We enjoyed a large room and bath with one double and two twin beds - all comfortable and no smoking! Our older sons had two twin beds and bath on the second floor. The staff is friendly and accomodating. We very much enjoyed our stay over Christmas. The basement breakfast room is lovely and although the breakfast bar selection is small, it is healthful and offers tea, coffee, toast, jam, muesli cereal, yogurt, fruit salad, cheese, crackers,sliced meat and during Christmas the traditional mince tarts. While modest, we found it far more preferable to the more common selection of pastries, eggs or sausages. The location was excellent as well. Only half a small block from Earl's Court tube stop and a happy selection of well priced restaurants on Earl's Court Road. The Rushmore is between both a Tesco and a Sainsbury (supermarkets) - both large, open late and in easy walking/bus distance. Communication with the hotel was efficient (Teresa) and reliable. We all felt the Rushmore was a 10 out of 10 Hotel and would love to return.	
